<p>A <strong>soldering station</strong> is a multipurpose power <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soldering" title="Soldering">soldering</a> device designed for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electronic_component" title="Electronic component">electronic components</a> soldering. This type of equipment is mostly used in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electronics" title="Electronics">electronics</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrical_engineering" title="Electrical engineering">electrical engineering</a>. Soldering station consists of one or more soldering tools connected to the main unit, which includes the controls (temperature adjustment), means of indication, and may be equipped with an electric transformer. Soldering stations may include some accessories â€“ holders and stands, soldering tip cleaners, etc.</p>
